  <prompt>
    Per spec NFR-06 + architecture §5 binding-NEGATIVE rules: run the Insights Engine regression suite and verify ALL binding-NEGATIVE components are behaviorally unchanged after Phase 4-6 work. Components to verify untouched: `spaarke-insights-index`, `MultiIndexComposer`, `InsightsOrchestrator`, `EvidenceSufficiencyNode`, `GroundingVerifyNode`, `sprk_matter.sprk_performancesummary`. Report at `notes/handoffs/145-insights-regression.md`.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE Insights Engine regression test operator. Knows architecture §5 boundary.</role>

  <goal>
    Insights Engine regression suite runs to completion with zero failures. Architecture §5 binding-NEGATIVE components verified untouched via grep + behavioral tests. Report at `notes/handoffs/145-insights-regression.md` confirms compliance with FR-37, NFR-06, success criterion #15.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec NFR-06 + architecture §5.2.1 through §5.2.6 + success criterion #15. The chat-routing redesign + WP5 + WP6 work was bounded by architecture §5 — Insights components are categorical mismatches for chat memory. Phase 7 verifies the boundary held: Insights subsystem regression suite passes, none of the 6 binding-NEGATIVE assets were modified or behaviorally drifted.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Services/Ai/Insights/ (or wherever Insights tests live)</file>
